And when we consider that other theory of the natural philosophers, that all other earthly hues every stately or lovely emblazoning the sweet tinges of sunset skies and woods; yea, and the gilded velvets of butterflies, and the butterfly cheeks of young girls; all these are but subtile deceits, not actually inherent in substances, but only laid on from without; so that all deified Nature absolutely paints like the harlot, whose allurements cover nothing but the charnel-house within; and when we proceed further, and consider that the mystical cosmetic which produces every one of her hues, the great principle of light, for ever remains white or colorless in itself, and if operating without medium upon matter, would touch all objects, even tulips and roses, with its own blank tinge pondering all this, the palsied universe lies before us a leper; and like wilful travellers in Lapland, who refuse to wear colored and coloring glasses upon their eyes, so the wretched infidel gazes himself blind at the monumental white shroud that wraps all the prospect around him. an orange cyclops-eye, scorning to look

cb8ce2c213-03-10 cb8ce2c2ROYGBIV Roy FAcb8ce2c2 cb8ce2c2First ascent. Great fun! Sick grips. This was established as a contrivance. That means, specifically, I thought about the possibility of using the jugs on the arete, but I intentionally did not use the jugs on the arete. I did not toe hook, grab, or otherwise use those holds. The second move is a jump to a bad sloping left hand pinch. Happy to share uncut footage of the FA if anyone would like to see. I don't care if people want to use the jugs on the arete, but it is not what I climbed. This was established as a contrivance, and if you're looking for 10 points, then those jugs are off. I realize that makes this problem not that great, but if you do use the jugs then why not top out there? The contrivance makes sense to me. If you do want to climb it with the jugs, be honest about what you've done, as that jump move is quite challenging. Also, for the love of god, I've been bouldering here for over 4 years. It's always been peaceful, quiet and clean. Suddenly with all the new internet spray, there are chipped holds, spliff butts, screwdrivers lying around, and stupid climbing stickers all over the NF gates, which were left opened by other climbers. Take care of this place!!! **cb8ce2c2

cf4b391108-11-10 cf4b3911Sing the Sorrow Newlin Soft, FAcf4b3911 cf4b3911First Ascent. The wall to the left of Walk Softly, from the sit start. There may have been a stand start climbed previously, but Sing the Sorrow is the name of the problem from the sit. I thought this felt like V10, because the day before I climbed Center Route in my tennis shoes. But as so often is the case, FAs feel harder than they usually are. But this problem is clearly easier, so grade chasers be damned! If you feel as though you are unsure as to how hard a "real" V10 should feel, go do Full Service, Trent's Mom, Whispers of Wisdom. V9 can be a lot harder than this, based on my experience. **cf4b3911
